added.title: Where Exactly on the Globe is Carl Sanpedro Part 1
added.description: The Titans fly to Los Angeles but end up in San Pedro, where Berto tells them about the villainous long shoreman, Carl Sanpedro.

added.title: Where Exactly on the Globe is Carl Sanpedro Part 2
added.description: Carl Sanpedro has struck again, this time in Jamaica, so the Titans take off for the Caribbean.

added.title: Where Exactly on the Globe is Carl SanPedro Part 3
added.description: The Titans travel to India to stop Carl Sanpedro and learn about the sport of cricket.

added.title: Where Exactly on the Globe is Carl SanPedro Part 4
added.description: In the final epic showdown with Carl Sanpedro, the Titans head to Croatia, the home of dragons and ice zombies.

added.title: Oh Yeah!
added.description: Cyborg tells the other Titans that TV wrestling is fake and tries to teach them about real wrestling.

added.title: Man Person
added.description: Despite the Titans' protests, Beast Boy becomes convinced that replacing his body parts with robotic limbs makes him more manly.

added.title: Dog Hand
added.description: Raven's supervillain father comes to visit and the rest of the team thinks he's the coolest...until he steals their souls.

added.title: The Date
added.description: Robin poses as Speedy to sabotage his upcoming date with Starfire.

added.title: Nose Mouth
added.description: The Titans overuse Raven's dark magic, causing unintended consequences.

added.title: Itch to Explore
added.description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

added.title: You're It
added.description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

added.title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
added.description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Wildernessa
added.description: An encounter with Wildernessa, guardian of the wilderness, inspires Kelsey to take up a cause.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Dad is in charge of getting the kids to their first day back at school on time, but he's overslept and now he can't find Gumball, Darwin or Anais anywhere. He sets about retracing his steps from the day before to work out where they might be.

added.title: The Check
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais are delighted when Grandpa Louie gives them a check for $5000. They immediately start fantasizing over what to spend it on. But when Mom and Dad say they're going to spend the money on paying bills instead, it's a race to the bank to see who can cash the check first.

added.title: The Comic
added.description: Gumball is the star of his own comic, but struggles to match up to his heroic alter-ego.

added.title: The Apprentice
added.description: Gumball decides that the best way to prove to Mr. Fitzgerald that he's good enough for Penny is to become his apprentice for the day. The problem is Mr. Fitzgerald has an important interview and Gumball's enthusiastic attempts to help him might actually do more harm than good, both to Mr. Fitzgerald's business and to Gumball's future with Penny.

added.title: The Advice
added.description: Mr. Small feels that he hasn't inspired the children of Elmore Junior High, so Gumball and Darwin try to lift his spirits.

added.title: The Music Store Thief
added.description: Apple and Onion have to defend the music store from instrument theft to get a key to the store.

added.title: The Fly
added.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

added.title: Dragonhead
added.description: Apple and Onion must run a secret parking lot on their roof terrace so they can have a shower.

added.title: Pulling Your Weight
added.description: Apple and Onion join a gym to gain the strength of seven people.

added.title: Folk Art Foes
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes the lord of mischief from an ancient relic, V and V have to work together to trap it back inside.

added.title: Legend of the Hidden Skate Park
added.description: While searching for a hidden skate park, V and V happen upon a tribe of wild kids, who live in a society without rules or adults.

added.title: The Babysitter
added.description: Vic & Val want to sneak out to a secret fireworks show but are thwarted when their new babysitter, Xochi, outsmarts them at every turn.

added.title: Suerte
added.description: When Vic cheats on an enchanted board game, the malevolent characters come to life, and it's up to V & V to figure out how to put them back in the game.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Gem Glow
added.description: Steven thinks his favorite ice cream sandwiches are the trick to summoning his magic shield but learns otherwise when facing off with an acid-spewing insect monster.

added.title: Frybo
added.description: Steven helps a Boardie kid with his grueling job by using a magical gem shard that can bring clothing to life.

added.title: Giant Woman
added.description: During a mission to the Sky Spire, Steven tries to convince Amethyst and Pearl to fuse together and become a giant woman.

added.title: Fusion Cuisine
added.description: In an effort to win over Connie's parents, Steven convinces the Gems to fuse together and pretend to be his mother.

added.title: Garnet's Universe
added.description: Steven imagines what Garnet does with her day.

added.title: Tiger Fail
added.description: Gwen refuses to be pressured into choosing an ice cream flavor that she does not want.

added.title: A Ninjustice to Harold
added.description: Harold's world is turned upside down when Beth becomes the class ninja.

added.title: Having the Timeout of Our Lives
added.description: Owen forms a special bond with Duncan after having loads of fun with him during their timeouts.

added.title: Hic Hic Hooray
added.description: Bridgette gets the hiccups and becomes desperate to get rid of them.

added.title: Bananas & Cheese
added.description: Duncan is determined to stop the musical duo Bananas & Cheese from coming to the daycare.

added.title: Inglorious Toddlers
added.description: Owen fears he's about to lose his BFF Noah to a gifted military school.

added.title: Not Without My Fudgy Lumps
added.description: Noah tries to rescue the chocolates Owen forgot outside.

added.title: Paint That a Shame
added.description: Leshawna creates a paint balloon fight to decide who gets to come with her to an amusement park.

added.title: Snots Landing
added.description: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

added.title: Know it All
added.description: Courtney must go all day without correcting her friends which is hard because they do everything wrong!

added.title: The Filth
added.description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

added.title: Waterfilter
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max's trip to Niagara Falls is cut short by the horrid Hydromanders, creatures menacing them and their fellow tourists.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: The Clocktopus
added.description: In a peaceful coastal town, Ben must not only face the archaic antagonist Steam Smythe and his latest creation, the Clocktopus, but also his deepest, darkest fear: Squids!

added.title: Take 10
added.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppe, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Animo Farm
added.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

added.title: Mao Mao's Nakey
added.description: When MM loses his clothes while trying to scale the Ruby Pure Heart, he has to get back to Sheriff's HQ by daybreak.

added.title: Lucky Ducky Mug
added.description: When Adorabat and Badgerclops break Mao Mao's favorite mug, he gives them the silent treatment.

added.title: Princess Monster Wife
added.description: When Ooo's princesses start losing body parts left and right, Finn and Jake investigate.

added.title: Princess Cookie
added.description: Finn and Jake are called on to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

added.title: King Worm
added.description: Finn has a particularly vivid dream, and all of Ooo is in it or does he?

added.title: Lady & Peebles
added.description: Princess Bubblegum and Lady Rainicorn go on a quest to find Finn and Jake who are missing after fighting the Ice King.

added.title: Reign of Gunters
added.description: The Gunters go on a rampage against the Ice King and the citizens of Ooo!

added.title: Ninja vs. Lava
added.description: The ninja find themselves trapped in a pyramid and must escape encroaching lava to warn NINJAGO City of a new Serpentine invasion.

added.title: Snaketastrophy
added.description: The Serpentine attack on NINJAGO City is seen from an unexpected perspective - entirely in the style of a live newscast delivered by Gayle Gossip and her cameraman.

added.title: Powerless
added.description: The ninja rush to the NINJAGO Museum of History to recover a dangerous scroll before it falls into the hands of the Serpentine Sorceress Aspheera.

added.title: Ancient History
added.description: While Aspheera pursues revenge on the "Treacherous Deceiver" who betrayed her, the ninja make a startling discovery.

added.title: KO, Rad, and Enid!
added.description: When confronted with their lack of a team gimmick, KO, Rad, and Enid wonder what their group identity should be.

added.title: K.O. vs Fink
added.description: When Fink taunts KO for being a momma's boy, he grapples with newfound insecurity about it.

added.title: Let's Get Shadowy
added.description: KO teams up with an unlikely ally to take on an old foe.

added.title: Let's Fight to the End
added.description: When a fighting tournament is announced at the Plaza, there is more at stake than meets the eye.

added.title: Benson's Car
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to fix Benson's car before he finds out they broke its window.

added.title: A Skips in Time
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Skips return Teenage Skips to the 1700s.

added.title: Bank Shot
added.description: Rigby has to win a bet by beating a guy at basketball bank shots.

added.title: Bad Portrait
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to re-paint Benson's portrait for a party.

added.title: Bachelor Party! Zingo!
added.description: Skips must plan the perfect bachelor party for his cousin, Quips.

added.title: Animal Day
added.description: Clarence feels the call of the wild - and decides to live a new life, free of the hustle and bustle of the modern world. Recruiting a few friends, Clarence sets out to find a new place to live his feral life, but quickly realizes he lacks some basic survival skills.

added.title: Talent Show
added.description: Clarence throws a big talent show in his yard to showcase all the fun hidden talents of his friends. But when Brady claims he's talentless, Clarence sets out to prove that everyone has something special to share!

added.title: Dog King Clarence
added.description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

added.title: Clarence the Movie
added.description: When Clarence starts to play around with his home video camera, he becomes increasingly drawn into the world of filmmaking. From talking toys, to real actors, to documentary subjects, Clarence is determined to find the right style to tell his story!

added.title: Brains TV
added.description: After a marathon of classic sitcom episodes, Clarence becomes stuck as alter-ego "Clarry," an obnoxiously overacting sitcom version of himself. It's up to his friends and family to help him snap out of it, or face life with a new Clarence.

added.title: The Little Mer-Tiger
added.description: The origin of Tiger is told as a flashback.  As the legend goes, Tiger used to be a mermaid.  One day the evil ruler of the sea, Bubble Grandpa, demanded a hamburger and picked Tiger to retrieve it.  He used his magic sea powers to give Tiger legs and send her ashore.  But Tiger grew to love the land, and with the help of her new friend, Uncle Grandpa, defeated the evil sea ruler and got to keep her legs.

added.title: Back to the Library
added.description: Uncle Grandpa uses time travel to convince his past self to return a library book on time.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Can't Buy Love
added.description: When Morbucks falls in love, she finds the first thing money can't buy.

added.title: Lame Station
added.description: Pizza Steve tries desperately to make the others in the RV interested in his new game console.

added.title: Relaxation Land
added.description: Uncle Grandpa's relaxing weekend getaway quickly becomes a spooky nightmare for Pizza Steve.

added.title: Under Wraps
added.description: When Ben and Gwen are sent to a farm to learn the value of hard work, what they really learn is that an evil alien mummy has arrived on Earth.

added.title: Bucketboy!
added.description: When the girls tell Barry he's a hero, he takes it too far.

added.title: Cat Burglar
added.description: An alarmingly familiar cat burglar terrorizes Townsville.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Artesanias traviesas
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic libera al señor de las travesuras del interior una reliquia antigua, V y V tienen que trabajar en equipo para volver a encerrarlo.

added.title: La Leyenda del Parque Patinetas
added.description: Mientras buscan un parque de patinaje escondido, V y V se encuentran con una tribu de niños salvajes, que viven en una sociedad sin reglas ni adultos.

added.title: El Libro Final
added.description: El último libro de fantasía de la serie favorita de Kelsey desaparece de la biblioteca. Por eso, Craig decide ayudarla a resolver el misterio de quién se lo llevó.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Demasiados Tesoros
added.description: Con la esperanza de reparar su fuerte, Craig consigue la ayuda de Los Veloces Diez para llevarlos hasta la legendaria pila de basura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Toma 10
added.description: Mientras Ben intenta rodar su propia película independiente, por accidente libera a una pandilla de insectos y, cuando la lucha se traslada a su guarida oculta, Ben debe enfrentarse a su líder narcisista: La Hormiga Reina.

added.title: Salvajessa
added.description: Un encuentro con Salvajessa, guardiana de la naturaleza, inspira a Kelsey a dedicarse a una causa.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Dog Daze/In Focus
added.description: Dog Daze: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor./In Focus: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

added.title: It Was Them
added.description: Dr. Animo has escaped his Plumber prison, and Ben and Rook must track him down before he turns the world into his personal mutant ant farm! (Introducing Nemetrix alien Slamworm, Galvan Plumbers Blukic and Driba, Arctiguana, new Ben alien Crashhopper.)

added.title: Cambio De Edad
added.description: Durante una parada en la megatienda Shoppë, Nanny Nightmare -una niñera que se volvió loca- transforma a Ben y Gwen en bebés. Y nada la detendrá en su intento de reorganizar el mundo a imagen y semejanza de su guardería.

added.title: La ninera
added.description: Vic y Val quieren colarse en un espectáculo secreto de fuegos artificiales, pero su plan se ve frustrado cuando su nueva niñera, Xochi, los supera en todo momento.

added.title: The Exit/The Lost and the Cost
added.description: The Exit: The AO compete with a rival Brawling team for ViewTube hits leading to a "winner take all" brawl./The Lost and the Cost: Everett Ray, a promotor, tries to get the AO to join an official league for Bakugan Battling.

added.title: Shhh
added.description: Mientras Ben se relaja en un monasterio con una política de silencio, no puede quedarse callado y, por accidente, despierta a un peligroso Dragón oculto en una recámara secreta bajo los salones sagrados...una tarea que podría ser demasiado para manejar, iincluso para Diamante!

added.title: Mr. Moon/What's Wrong with Dan
added.description: Mr. Moon: Wynton finds a new Bakugan who proves difficult to control but things get more complicated when Col. Tripp seizes control of Trox./What's Wrong with Dan: With "Dan" behaving strangely toward the AO Lightning sniffs out the truth- an impostor!

added.title: Hot Stretch
added.description: Ben and Rook encounter a race of elastic, hot-blooded aliens in Undertown who want to use a stolen nuclear fusion engine to activate a volcano! (Introducing Ester, Seebik & the Kraaho.)

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Loteria
added.description: Cuando Vic hace trampa en un juego de mesa encantado, los malvados personajes cobran vida, y V y V son los responsables de averiguar cómo volver a ponerlos en el juego.

added.title: Impotente
added.description: El ninja corre al Museo de Historia de NINJAGO para recuperar un pergamino peligroso antes de que caiga en manos de la Hechicera Serpentina Aspheera.

added.title: La Breve Carrera De La Nina Suertuda
added.description: Cuando un hechicero jugador de cosplay pone las manos sobre una varita mágica real en la convención Comic Con, Ben consigue la ayuda de Gwen para impedir que Hex la recupere: Gwen engaña al hechicero malvado y le hace creer que es una poderosa maga...ila única e inimitable Niña Suertuda!

added.title: Babysitting Bedlam/Rubbed the Wrong Way
added.description: Rubbed the Wrong Way: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day./Babysitting Bedlam: Dan and Wynton meet a strange boy who leads them into an underground maze where they discover the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

added.title: Historia Antigua
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Rebelion En La Granja
added.description: Ben encuentra el laboratorio secreto del Doctor Ánimo -ahora gobernado por los alfas, sus mutantes superiores- y debe ayudar a los animales inferiores mientras está atrapado en forma de Insectoide.

added.title: Mask of Power/Story Holes
added.description:
Mask of Power: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan./Story Holes:  
A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan but they soon realize the call was actually a test from a mysterious benefactor.

added.title: Enredos perrunos
added.description: Lightning descubre un nuevo Bakugan, Artulean, y eso desata una fuerte rivalidad entre él y Howlkor.

added.title: Bajo los reflectores
added.description: Cuando la reportera Verónica Venegas, madre de Lia, hace un reportaje acerca de Los Fantásticos, Strata El Cazador intenta capturar a Hydorous.

added.title: Many Happy Returns
added.description: Gwen and Kevin pay Ben a surprise visit, but does Kevin's strange behavior have anything to do with an angry Tetramand princess, or her father's fleet of warships prepared to attack the Earth?

added.title: Side Effects
added.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

added.title: El equipo Exit
added.description: Los Fantásticos compiten por el número de visitas en sus videos con un equipo rival llamado "El equipo Exit" en una batalla donde se juegan el todo por el todo.

added.title: Perdidas y ganancias
added.description: Un promotor llamado Everett Ray quiere convencer a Los Fantásticos de ingresar a una liga oficial de Batallas Bakugan.

added.title: Sr. Luna
added.description: Wynton encuentra un nuevo Bakugan que resulta difícil de controlar, y las cosas se complican cuando el Coronel Tripp se apodera de Trox.

added.title: Que ocurre con Dan
added.description: Cuando Dan se comporta de forma extraña con los Fantásticos, Lightning olfatea la verdad: iUn impostor!

added.title: Frenemy
added.description: When the coolest girl in school befriends the girls, she charms them into becoming her accomplices in a series of adventurous crimes.

added.title: Una necesidad inquietante
added.description: La aparición de un nuevo campo Bakugan hace que los chicos del pueblo corran a buscar a sus propios Bakugan. Pero cuando el campo es contaminado, Lia debe salvarlos a todos.

added.title: Tutores Bakugan
added.description: Dan y Wynton conocen a un extraño chico que los lleva a un laberinto subterráneo, donde descubren que el Bakugan del chico ha sido esclavizado.

added.title: #SuperHeroBoys Parte 1
added.description: Lo que comienza como una simple investigación por vandalismo, se transforma en una lucha territorial cuando las chicas encuentran un poderoso trío de kryptonianos decididos a dominar el mundo, y lo que es peor... iun grupo de Super Hero Boys!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Ninos vergonzosos
added.description: Owen teme perder a su mejor amigo Noah que se va a una escuela militar.

added.title: Mascara de poder
added.description: Philomena Dusk, de la Corporación AAAnimus, contrata a Magnus y le implanta un dispositivo que aumenta el poder de su Bakugan para derrotar a Dan.

added.title: No sin mis choco-lletas
added.description: Noah intenta rescatar los chocolates que Owen olvidó afuera.

added.title: #DCSuperHeroBoys Part 1
added.description: What begins as a simple vandalism investigation becomes an all-out turf war when the team encounters a powerful trio of Kryptonians bent on world domination, and, perhaps even worse, a rival team of SUPER HERO BOYS!

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Una verdad a medias
added.description: Un críptico correo electrónico lleva a Los Fantásticos en busca de un Bakugan desaparecido, pero pronto se dan cuenta de que el correo era una prueba de un misterioso benefactor.

added.title: Pintura dolorosa
added.description: Leshawna inventa una pelea con globos llenos de pintura para ver quién va al parque de diversiones con ella.

added.title: Aterrizaje mocoso
added.description: A Beth se le atascan los muebles del diorama de Courtney en la nariz y Courtney tiene que recuperarlos antes de que llegue el juez del concurso de dioramas.

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Courtney debe pasar todo el día sin corregir a sus amigos, y eso es difícil porque lo hacen todo mal.

added.title: To Air Is Robot
added.description: Air Man stakes a claim on the skies above Silicon City, threatening anything that trespasses on his airspace.

added.title: Watt's Happening?!
added.description: When Elec Man derails the school play by hijacking Silicon Central's power, Aki/Mega Man must use what he has learned onstage to defeat his supercharged foe.

added.title: Chill Out, Bruh
added.description: Aki and Suna take a rehabilitated Ice Man out for a day in the city, but things take a turn for the worse as he misinterprets their cues and turns a game of hover hockey into a literal freeze out!

added.title: Big Bad Dreams
added.description: When Namagem starts using his Hypno powers to haunt Aki's dreams, our hero must face his fears in the dreamscape.

added.title: License to Drill
added.description: Mega Man teams up with Bert Wily to take down Drill Man, whose plan to construct hundreds of drill shaped high rises has put Silicon City in both aesthetic and physical danger!

added.title: Collect This
added.description: Ben finally meets the ones responsible for his intergalactic TV show, and the actor who makes Ben 10 more famous than Ben himself!

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: #IllusionsOfGrandeur
added.description: Ready to emerge from her father's shadow, Zee Zatara secretly seeks fame and acclaim performing for her own audience at the pier. But when her act is dismissed as fakery, she loses her cool and accidentally unleashes mischievous gremlins who run wild all over the pier.

added.title: #BeastsInShow
added.description: When Babs and Kara spar over whose dog is better, they decide to settle it at the Metropolis Dog Show, where Ace the Bat-Hound and Krypto the Superdog suddenly find themselves called upon to save the day… in more ways than one.

added.title: Here Comes Haavik/The Fusion Bakugan Arrive
added.description: Here Comes Haavik: An evil shapeshifting alien has landed in Los Volmos! If that wasn't bad enough, he has a group of robot mechanoids on his trail trying to bring him justice. Meanwhile, Dan has accepted a battle challenge from a pair of brawlers, Chad and Trey./The Fusion Bakugan Arrive: Still humiliated by their defeat, Chad and Trey challenge Dan to rematch but this time they have a few tricks up their sleeve, and a little help on their side.

added.title: The Director/Queen Ebony
added.description: The Director: Everett Ray reaches out to Lia with an opportunity that seems too good to be true. Everett is now working in show business and proposes to make Lia's dream of becoming a film director come true. He's taken care of all the arrangements; all Lia has to do is provide the directorial vision./Queen Ebony: On his daily jaunt, Lightning learns of a street cat named Ebony, who's been treating dogs like servants, threatening them to do her bidding or face the wrath of her Bakugan! Lightning tries to reason with Ebony but when that doesn't work, it turns into a cat vs. dog Bakugan brawl!

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Minus Mini
added.description: When Mega Mini is kidnapped by Blasto Woman, Mega Man must track down his missing partner without the full use of his own systems.

added.title: A Cut Above
added.description: Aki and Bert accidentally damage a bonsai tree outside the Lighthouse, sending the Lights' perfectionist gardener on a slicing-and-dicing spree as Cut Man.

added.title: A Bot and His Dog
added.description: Tired of fielding of low stakes house calls, Mega Man gets what he wishes for when Hypno Woman hijacks the local power plant.

added.title: This Man, This Man Man!
added.description: When Guts Man goes on a ravenous rampage across the city, Mega Man must turn to an unlikely ally, Man Man, a bumbling DIY human analog to our hero.

added.title: A Guilded Cage
added.description: Mega Man must stop Namagem and an army of hypnotized Good Guild bots from breaking into Dr. Light's lab.

added.title: La Suciedad
added.description: A Ben le encargan la tarea de limpiar la Chatarra, pero cuando, engañado por los viles villanos Fly Guys, permite que se lo roben, debe perseguirlos antes de que fabriquen una larva monstruosa imparable con un objetivo claro: destruir Las Vegas.

added.title: Ganas de Explorar
added.description: La misión de Craig de mapear el Arroyo entero los lleva a él y a sus amigos a arboleda traicionera de Hiedra Venenosa
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Filtro Acuatico
added.description: El viaje de Ben, Gwen y Max a las Cataratas del Niágara se ve interrumpido por los horribles Hydromanders: unas criaturas que los amenazan a ellos y a los demás turistas.

added.title: La Traes
added.description: Un despiadado juego de persecución desata un caos en el Arroyo, y se declara a Kelsey como la próxima perseguidora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Jessica va al Arroyo
added.description: Cuando Craig y Jessica quedan encerrados fuera de la casa, Craig no tiene otra opción: debe llevar a su hermanita al Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Lider Del Ring
added.description: Cuando Ben tiene una racha ganadora en un videojuego, se le ocurre una idea para ganar un partido real de lucha, hasta que un luchador intimidante decide convertirlo en un verdadero desafío.

added.title: Sobreviviendo A La Tormenta
added.description: El campamento de Ben y Gwen se ve interrumpido por los gélidos Weatherheads -Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o-, pero un Omnitrix que funciona mal y dispara un montón de extraterrestres podría no ser un pronóstico de éxito.

added.title: El bravucon
added.description: Los Fantásticos deben lidiar con un bravucón que usa a su Bakugan para intimidar a los chicos del vecindario.

added.title: El Relopulpo
added.description: En una pacífica ciudad costera, Ben no solo debe enfrentarse a Vapor Smythe -su arcaico antagonista- y a su última creación, el Relopulpo... isino que también debe enfrentarse a su temor más profundo y oscuro: los calamares!

added.title: Bromas pesadas
added.description: Las constantes bromas pesadas de Wynton colman la paciencia de su Bakugan, Trox, quien decide darle una lección.

added.title: Ninja Contra Lava
added.description: Los ninja se encuentran atrapados en una pirámide y deben escapar de la lava invasora para advertir a la ciudad de NINJAGO de una nueva invasión serpentina.

added.title: Heroes locales
added.description: Los Fantásticos provocan una ola de destrucción por accidente, y los padres de Dan se preguntan si deberían permitirle a los niños conservar sus Bakugan.

added.title: Pegatrix
added.description: Lia no concuerda con las técnicas de Pegatrix, pero durante una intensa batalla, debe aprender a confiar en los conocimientos de su Bakugan.

added.title: Serpientastrofe
added.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

added.title: Ene-amigos
added.description: Dos nuevos Peleadores Bakugan, Shun y Magnus, buscan ser parte de Los Fantásticos.

added.title: El miedo de Strata
added.description: Los Fantásticos resuelven la misteriosa desaparición del Bakugan de un niño, y conocen a un cazador de Bakugan llamado Strata.

added.title: Fallo de tigre
added.description: Gwen se niega a que la presionen para elegir un sabor de helado que no quiere.

added.title: Una ninja justicia para Harold
added.description: El mundo de Harold queda de cabeza cuando sus compañeros declaran que Beth es la verdadera ninja de la clase.

added.title: El castigo de mi vida
added.description: Owen forma un nexo especial con Duncan después de que ambos se divirtieran mucho durante sus castigos.

added.title: #IlusionesDeGrandeza
added.description: Lista para salir de la sombra de su padre, Zatara busca la fama y el reconocimiento con una presentación para su propia audiencia en el muelle. Pero cuando su acto es tildado de fraude, ella pierde el control y accidentalmente libera terribles seres que causan estragos en el muelle.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Hip hip Hurra
added.description: Bridgette tiene hipo y está desesperada por librarse de ellos.

added.title: Bananas y Queso
added.description: Duncan está decidido a evitar que el dúo Banana y Queso se presente en la guardería.

removed.description: Un divertido día para Barbara Gordon y su mejor amiga Harley Quinzel en la Convención Anual de Gotham City, es puesto cabeza abajo cuando, de la nada, ila malvada Harley Quinn aparece para sembrar el caos! Por suerte para todos, Batgirl se encuentra casualmente en el área...

removed.title: Try Hard
removed.description: When the Sky Pirates take Mao Mao and Badgerclops hostage, it's up to Adorabat to save the day.
